elDS1CMChannelNumber.name: elDS1CMChannelNumber
elDS1CMChannelNumber.description: Table index, the DS1 channel number.

elDS1CMLineCode.name: elDS1CMLineCode
elDS1CMLineCode.description: Select DS1 line code for the channel number selected by this tables index.

elDS1CMLineBuildout.name: elDS1CMLineBuildout
elDS1CMLineBuildout.description: Select line build-out for the DS1 line selected by this tables index:, 0 to 133 ft, or 133 to 266 ft, 266 to 399 ft, 399 to 533 ft, or 533 to 655 ft.

elDS1CMLoopbackMode.name: elDS1CMLoopbackMode
elDS1CMLoopbackMode.description: Set the DS1 loopback mode to Line, terminal, remote, or none. In M13 Mode, issuing a DS1 Remote Terminal Lpbk will cause any previous Remote DS1 Terminal Lpbk(s) to be Dropped.

elDS1CMServiceMode.name: elDS1CMServiceMode
elDS1CMServiceMode.description: Set the DS1 service mode for the channel indicated to in-service or out-of-service. Certain service effecting operations can not be initiated unless the DS1 channel is placed out-of-service.

elDS1CMInterfaceEquipped.name: elDS1CMInterfaceEquipped
elDS1CMInterfaceEquipped.description: DS1 Interfaces may be 'equipped' or 'unequipped'. No PM or FM operations will occur on an unequipped interface. Access is allowed to MIB variables which correspond to unequipped interfaces, although PM and FM values will be zeros. When the DS1 interface is Disaled an AIS will be sent on the channel.

elDS1CMChannelName.name: elDS1CMChannelName
elDS1CMChannelName.description: A ChannelName can be assigned for each DS1 channel. The Channel name cannot be more than 10 characters.

elDS1CMInputStatus.name: elDS1CMInputStatus
elDS1CMInputStatus.description: Reports the input State of the DS1 channel indexed by Channel Number.

elDS1CMMaskState.name: elDS1CMMaskState
elDS1CMMaskState.description: Get the state of the DS1 Channel identified by the index. The Mask state identifies the Autosense State of the DS1 Channel.

elDS1CMInterfaceRescan.name: elDS1CMInterfaceRescan
elDS1CMInterfaceRescan.description: Rescan the DS1 Channel identified by the index.

elALLDS1CMLineCode.name: elALLDS1CMLineCode
elALLDS1CMLineCode.description: Set DS1 line code for all DS1 channels. A value Inderminate(3) will be returned if All the DS1 Channels are not set to either ds1LineCodeAMI or ds1LineCodeB8ZS.

elALLDS1CMLineBuildout.name: elALLDS1CMLineBuildout
elALLDS1CMLineBuildout.description: Select line build-out for All the DS1 lines to 0 to 133 ft, or 133 to 266 ft, 266 to 399 ft, 399 to 533 ft, or 533 to 655 ft.

elALLDS1CMLoopbackMode.name: elALLDS1CMLoopbackMode
elALLDS1CMLoopbackMode.description: Set the DS1 loopback mode to Line, Terminal, Remote, or None for All the DS1 Channels. In M13 Mode, issuing a DS1 Remote Terminal Lpbk will cause any previous Remote DS1 Terminal Lpbk(s) to be dropped.

elALLDS1CMServiceMode.name: elALLDS1CMServiceMode
elALLDS1CMServiceMode.description: Set the DS1 service mode for All DS1 channels to in-service or out-of-service. Certain service effecting operations can not be initiated unless All the DS1 channels will be placed out-of-service.

elALLDS1CMInterfaceEquipped.name: elALLDS1CMInterfaceEquipped
elALLDS1CMInterfaceEquipped.description: Set All the DS1 Channels to 'equipped' or 'unequipped' state. No PM or FM operations will occur on an unequipped DS1 interface. Access is allowed to MIB variables which correspond to unequipped interfaces, although PM and FM values will be zeros.

elCMSystemStatus.name: elCMSystemStatus
elCMSystemStatus.description: This DisplayString gives the summary information about the Current EdgeLink100 System Status. The Description includes ... 1) chasisType --- UnProtected(1) / Protected(0) 2) Active Module --- Card-A(1) / Card-B (2) 3) Fault LED Status --- ON(1 -7) / OFF(0) 4) Abnormal LED Status --- ON(1) / OFF(0). Fault LED Status is a combined value of the three bits each representing CRITICAL, MAJOR and MINOR Alarms. The three LEDS are inside the EL100 Case on the Cards. 0 => No Alarms. 1 => Critical Alarm (001) 2 => Major Alarm (010) 3 => Critical and Major Alarms (011) 4 => Minor Alarm (100) 5 => Minor and Critical Alarms (101) 6 => Minor and Major Alarms (110) 7 => Major Minor and Critical Alarms (111).

elCMDS3ParityMode.name: elCMDS3ParityMode
elCMDS3ParityMode.description: Select C-bit or P-bit parity mode for DS3 interface. This Object can't be set when ServiceMode is IN-Service

elCMDS3LineBuildout.name: elCMDS3LineBuildout
elCMDS3LineBuildout.description: Select line build-out for DS3 Line, 0 to 100 ft, 100 to 200 ft, or 200-450.This MIB Object can't be set when ServiceMode is IN-Service

elCMDS3TxTiming.name: elCMDS3TxTiming
elCMDS3TxTiming.description: Select mode for DS3 transmit timing. This MIB Object can't be set when ServiceMode is IN-Service

elCMProtectionMode.name: elCMProtectionMode
elCMProtectionMode.description: In unprotected mode, switching is prohibited. While in protected mode, a standing minor alarm will occur if the off-line card is unavailable or not in operation. The system can be set to unprotected mode to turnoff this alarm. If the off-line card becomes operational while in unprotected mode, the mode is automatically switched to protected mode. The user will not be allowed to set the system to protectedMode.

elCMCardSelect.name: elCMCardSelect
elCMCardSelect.description: Read or select choice of on-line card. This operation will force a switch to occur if the off-line card is selected.

elCMClearTooManySwitches.name: elCMClearTooManySwitches
elCMClearTooManySwitches.description: Clear switching-disabled state which occurs as a result of too many switches between the cards in a protected system in a 10 minute interval. ClearTooManySwitchesLock command is used to remove the standing Alarm. On a read, the value indeterminate will be returned if the SNMP variable was never set to clearTooManySwitchesLock(2), otherwise clearTooManySwitchesLock(2) will be returned.

elCMDS3LoopbackMode.name: elCMDS3LoopbackMode
elCMDS3LoopbackMode.description: Set the DS3 loopback mode to line, terminal, remote, or none. The System can't be set to ds3LpbkRemoteFacility when it is in M13 Mode. The Terminal LoopBack is feasible only when the elCMDS3TxTiming Object is set to ds3TxTimingLocal.

elCMDS3ServiceMode.name: elCMDS3ServiceMode
elCMDS3ServiceMode.description: Set the DS3 service mode to in-service or out-of-service. Certain service effecting operations can not be initiated unless the DS3 channel is placed out-of-service.

elCMCurTimeDate.name: elCMCurTimeDate
elCMCurTimeDate.description: Read or set the system real time clock. The string is in the form MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM:SS.

elCMBerThreshold.name: elCMBerThreshold
elCMBerThreshold.description: Set the BER Threshold value for the system to 10-6, 10-7, 10-8 or 10-9. BerThershold can't changed when the ServiceMode is IN-Service.

elCMSystemInfo.name: elCMSystemInfo
elCMSystemInfo.description: Gets information about the MPU type, board revision, card revision level, software revision, CLEI code, MAC address, and Date of manufacture.

elCMPPPPortBaudRate.name: elCMPPPPortBaudRate
elCMPPPPortBaudRate.description: Specifies the baud rate on the craft/PPP port when that port is running PPP (i.e. when carrier detect is asserted).

elCMRemoteCBitIPAddress.name: elCMRemoteCBitIPAddress
elCMRemoteCBitIPAddress.description: This is the IP address of the partner EdgeLink's C-bit channel interface. This is used for partner-to-partner communications. Must be on same subnet as elCMLocalCBitIPAddress. This IP must be the same as elCMLocalCBitIPAddress on the partner device.

elCMLocalCBitIPAddress.name: elCMLocalCBitIPAddress
elCMLocalCBitIPAddress.description: This is the IP address of my C-bit channel interface and is used for partner-to-partner communications. Must be on same subnet as elCMRemoteCBitIPAddress. This IP must be the same as elCMRemoteCBitIPAddress on the partner device.

elCMCBitIPSubnetMask.name: elCMCBitIPSubnetMask
elCMCBitIPSubnetMask.description: Specifies the subnet address mask for the C-Bit IP channel.

elCMRemotePPPIPAddress.name: elCMRemotePPPIPAddress
elCMRemotePPPIPAddress.description: This is the IP Address for the Remote Client during PPP session.

elCMIfcInterfaceNumber.name: elCMIfcInterfaceNumber
elCMIfcInterfaceNumber.description: Table index. The table has one row for each external IP interface, Ethernet and PPP.

elCMIfcMyIPAddr.name: elCMIfcMyIPAddr
elCMIfcMyIPAddr.description: The IP address for this interface.

elCMIfcMyIPSubnetAddrMask.name: elCMIfcMyIPSubnetAddrMask
elCMIfcMyIPSubnetAddrMask.description: Subnet address mask for this IP address.

elCMIfcMyDefaultGatewayAddr.name: elCMIfcMyDefaultGatewayAddr
elCMIfcMyDefaultGatewayAddr.description: Default gateway address for this interface. If 0, it will be ignored.

elCMIfcTrapSendAddr1.name: elCMIfcTrapSendAddr1
elCMIfcTrapSendAddr1.description: Address 1 of 4 to send traps to. If 0, will be ignored.

elCMIfcTrapSendAddr2.name: elCMIfcTrapSendAddr2
elCMIfcTrapSendAddr2.description: Address 2 of 4 to send traps to. If 0, will be ignored.

elCMIfcTrapSendAddr3.name: elCMIfcTrapSendAddr3
elCMIfcTrapSendAddr3.description: Address 3 of 4 to send traps to. If 0, will be ignored.

elCMIfcTrapSendAddr4.name: elCMIfcTrapSendAddr4
elCMIfcTrapSendAddr4.description: Address 4 of 4 to send traps to. If 0, will be ignored.

elPMDS3TotalSwitches.name: elPMDS3TotalSwitches
elPMDS3TotalSwitches.description: Number of switches which have occurred since startup, or since last time PM metrics were cleared.

elPMClearAllPMMetrics.name: elPMClearAllPMMetrics
elPMClearAllPMMetrics.description: Clears all Performance Management related metrics and statistics. On a read, the value indeterminate(1) will be returned if this variable was never set to clearAllPMMetrics(2), otherwise clearAllPMMetrics(2) will be returned.

elDS1PMTimeElapsed.name: elDS1PMTimeElapsed
elDS1PMTimeElapsed.description: The number of elapsed seconds in the current interval of DS1 PM data.

elDS1PMValidIntervals.name: elDS1PMValidIntervals
elDS1PMValidIntervals.description: The number of intervals which have elapsed and for which PM data can read, up to and including 96.

elDS1PMCurEntry.name: elDS1PMCurEntry
elDS1PMCurEntry.description: DS1 current PM metrics table entry.

elDS1PMCurChannelNumber.name: elDS1PMCurChannelNumber
elDS1PMCurChannelNumber.description: Table index. Rows are indexed by DS1 channel.

elDS1PMCurLineCodeViolations.name: elDS1PMCurLineCodeViolations
elDS1PMCurLineCodeViolations.description: Number of line code violations in the current 15 minute interval.

elDS1PMCurErroredSeconds.name: elDS1PMCurErroredSeconds
elDS1PMCurErroredSeconds.description: Number of errored seconds in the current interval.

elDS1PMIvlEntry.name: elDS1PMIvlEntry
elDS1PMIvlEntry.description: DS1 Interval PM metrics table entry.

elDS1PMIvlChannelNumber.name: elDS1PMIvlChannelNumber
elDS1PMIvlChannelNumber.description: Primary table index, a DS1 channel number.

elDS1PMIvlIntervalNumber.name: elDS1PMIvlIntervalNumber
elDS1PMIvlIntervalNumber.description: Secondary table index, the interval number.

elDS1PMIvlLineCodeViolations.name: elDS1PMIvlLineCodeViolations
elDS1PMIvlLineCodeViolations.description: Number of line code violations for the channel specified by elDS1PMIvlChannelNumber and in the interval indicated by elDS1PMIvlIntervalNumber.

elDS1PMIvlErroredSeconds.name: elDS1PMIvlErroredSeconds
elDS1PMIvlErroredSeconds.description: Number of errored seconds for the channel specified by elDS1PMIvlChannelNumber and in the interval indicated by elDS1PMIvlIntervalNumber.

elDS1PMTotEntry.name: elDS1PMTotEntry
elDS1PMTotEntry.description: DS1 Total PM metrics table entry.

elDS1PMTotLineCodeViolations.name: elDS1PMTotLineCodeViolations
elDS1PMTotLineCodeViolations.description: Total number of line code violations for the channel specified by elDS1PMIvlChannelNumber.

elDS1PMTotErroredSeconds.name: elDS1PMTotErroredSeconds
elDS1PMTotErroredSeconds.description: Total number of errored seconds for the channel specified by elDS1PMIvlChannelNumber.

elFMFillAlarmLogTable.name: elFMFillAlarmLogTable
elFMFillAlarmLogTable.description: Take a snapshot of the alarm log. Must be done before reading the log into the alarm log table, elFMAlmLogTable. On a read, the value indeterminate(1) will be returned if the SNMP variable was never set to fillAlarmLogTable(2), otherwise fillAlarmLogTable(2) will be returned.

elFMClearAlarmLog.name: elFMClearAlarmLog
elFMClearAlarmLog.description: Clears the system's alarm log. On a read, the value indeterminate(1) will be returned if the SNMP variable was never set to clearAlarmLog(2) otherwise clearAlarmLog(2) will be returned.

elFMDS1AutoSenseMode.name: elFMDS1AutoSenseMode
elFMDS1AutoSenseMode.description: The AutoSense Mode will be enabled or Disabled on all the 28 Ds1 channels. The Rescan command will scan all the equipped DS1 Inputs and update their state.

elFMDS1InputAlarmMode.name: elFMDS1InputAlarmMode
elFMDS1InputAlarmMode.description: This command changes the severity of the DS1 LOS as either Major alarm or status depending on the selection.

elFMAlmLogTable.name: elFMAlmLogTable
elFMAlmLogTable.description: Alarm log table. This table holds a snapshot of the alarm log, and is filled by elFMFillAlarmLogTable.

elFMAlmLogTableTimestamp.name: elFMAlmLogTableTimestamp
elFMAlmLogTableTimestamp.description: Alarm time stamp in the form mm/dd/yy hh:mm:ss.

elFMAlmLogTableChannel.name: elFMAlmLogTableChannel
elFMAlmLogTableChannel.description: Channel associated with the alarm, if any.

elFMCurAlmTableAlarmNumber.name: elFMCurAlmTableAlarmNumber
elFMCurAlmTableAlarmNumber.description: Primary table index, an alarm number.

elFMCurAlmTableChannel.name: elFMCurAlmTableChannel
elFMCurAlmTableChannel.description: Secondary table index. Channel associated with the alarm, can be 0 if channel number is irrelevant to the alarm.

elFMTrapAlarmNumber.name: elFMTrapAlarmNumber
elFMTrapAlarmNumber.description: Alarm number associated with the last sent trap.

elFMTrapAlarmText.name: elFMTrapAlarmText
elFMTrapAlarmText.description: Alarm text associated with the last sent trap.

elFMTrapTimeStamp.name: elFMTrapTimeStamp
elFMTrapTimeStamp.description: Time stamp associated with the last sent trap.

elFMTrapAlarmStatus.name: elFMTrapAlarmStatus
elFMTrapAlarmStatus.description: Alarm status associated with the last sent trap.

elFMTrapChannelNumber.name: elFMTrapChannelNumber
elFMTrapChannelNumber.description: Channel number associated with the last sent trap, if any.

edgeLinkEvent.name: edgeLinkEvent
edgeLinkEvent.description: This trap is sent when an alarm event is set or cleard.
